        <h2>Why AEO Matters for SMEs</h2>
        <p><strong>Answer engine optimisation levels the playing field for small businesses by rewarding content quality and structural clarity over domain authority and budget.</strong> Traditional SEO is partly a function of how many quality backlinks a site has accumulated — a metric that naturally favours established, well-resourced brands. AEO, by contrast, rewards the site whose content most directly and clearly answers a specific query.</p>
        <p>When a user asks Google "how much does a boiler service cost in Manchester" or asks their voice assistant "who are the best accountants for freelancers in Bristol," the answer engine selects a source based on relevance, clarity, and structural signals — not primarily on domain age or link count. A specialist SME with well-structured, locally relevant content can outperform a national brand whose generic pages bury the answer in paragraphs of boilerplate.</p>
        <p>The scale of the opportunity is growing. AI Overviews now appear on a significant proportion of informational and commercial queries. Voice search usage continues to expand, with smart speakers and mobile voice queries growing year on year. Each of these touchpoints represents a zero-click visibility channel where small businesses can appear alongside — or in place of — much larger competitors, at zero cost per impression.</p>
        <p>For a comprehensive understanding of the broader discipline this sits within, see our guide to <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a>. AEO is the branch of GEO focused specifically on direct-answer selection, which makes it the natural starting point for SMEs with constrained resources.</p>
      </section>

