      <!-- Section 4: Content Restructuring -->
      <section id="content-restructuring" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Content Restructuring: The Highest-Leverage AEO Tactic</h2>
        <p><strong>Restructuring existing content is the single highest-ROI AEO action available to an SME because it converts pages you already rank for into answer positions.</strong> You do not need new content — you need the same content rearranged so answer engines can extract the core response efficiently.</p>
        <p>The fundamental restructuring pattern is the inverted pyramid: lead every page section with a single, definitive statement (40–60 words) that directly answers the implicit question behind the heading, then follow with supporting detail, examples, and nuance. This is the opposite of how most service-page copy is written, where context and background lead and the answer is buried two paragraphs down.</p>

        <h3>The Three Structural Changes That Matter Most</h3>
        <p><strong>Question-based H2s and H3s.</strong> Change "Our Services" to "What services does [business name] offer?" Change "The Process" to "How does the [service] process work?" Answer engines match heading text to query intent. Question headings dramatically improve the likelihood that the content beneath will be selected as a featured snippet or People Also Ask response. See our <a href="/aeo-best-practices/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AEO best practices guide</a> for detailed heading patterns.</p>
        <p><strong>Concise definitional openings.</strong> The first paragraph after each heading should stand alone as a complete answer to the heading question. Write it as if you were answering verbally: clear, direct, and free of preamble. Avoid phrases like "In this section, we will explore..." — answer engines extract the content, not the signposting.</p>
        <p><strong>FAQ sections on every service page.</strong> A dedicated FAQ section at the bottom of each service or location page, with 4–6 genuine questions and self-contained answers, creates multiple discrete answer opportunities per page. Each FAQ answer is independently eligible for featured-snippet and PAA selection. For examples of effective FAQ formats, see our <a href="/aeo-examples/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AEO examples</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 5: Schema on a Budget -->
